The paper proposes a deep-neural-network model for real-time traffic accident prediction using various data attributes such as traffic events, weather data, points-of-interest, and time. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper also discusses the creation of a large-scale publicly available database of accident information, which could fall under the sub-category of cybersecurity and privacy (cs.CR) or social and information networks (cs.SI).
